The paper deals with channel estimation and beamforming techniques for multiuser massive MIMO systems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also considers the tradeoff between training duration and throughput, which is a system-level optimization problem and falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the use of limited RF chains, which is a hardware constraint and falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Computer Communications (cs.COM) sub-categories.
